messages.text: Taylor waits alone in the hospital room.
The white sterile sheets are gathered tightly against her belly.
Jesus, please tell me you‚Äôre all right.
She can‚Äôt call her parents, not after what she did.
She can‚Äôt talk to Jonathan. Not this time.
Instead, she calls the one person she needs to stop running from.
Don‚Äôt worry. I‚Äôm on my way.
It‚Äôll take him fifteen minutes to get to the hospital.
Twenty with traffic ‚Äî and more if he‚Äôs far away.
Taylor looks at the clock. It‚Äôs only been seven minutes.
With each breath, fresh tears splatter against the sheets.
She checks the texts she sent Blake.
Room 2126. It‚Äôll be on your right in Labor and Delivery.
I‚Äôm only ten weeks pregnant, Blake ‚Äî that‚Äôs too soon to be here.
The phone buzzes in her hand.
You‚Äôre not a little girl anymore‚Ä¶you can‚Äôt just run away.
More tears fall, this time faster.
Do you have ANY IDEA how much money you wasted?
Taylor buries her face in her hands, crying harder.
Blake sits on the bed beside her and places his hand gently on her shoulder.
Blake‚Äôs hand slips from Taylor‚Äôs shoulder.
He walks toward the window, rubbing his face hard.
Is that what that stupid doctor told you?
What could you possibly have done wrong?
I ran out of the church, Blake.
No. Women run during pregnancy all the time.
That one woman ran a marathon pregnant.
I did this ‚Äî to our baby and to us.
Taylor shifts over when Blake slides into bed with her.
For a long few minutes they sit in silence, holding each other and crying softly.
I was under a lot of stress these last few days.
Or because you were marrying me?
It wasn‚Äôt supposed to be like this.
Jonathan told me he loves you.
Blake stares at their entwined fingers.
We were supposed to get married.
You and I were supposed to make babies.
And live happily ever after, right?
That‚Äôs what they always told us.
No, this is as bad is it gets.
I mean, I wasn‚Äôt ready to be a mother.
I wasn‚Äôt ready to be a father, either.
That doesn‚Äôt mean I didn‚Äôt love him.
I was sure it was a girl.
And I was sure it was a boy.
You were going to be a good dad.
You‚Äôre the best person I know.
I wish I could believe you.
Just like I wish I could believe in us.
Are you saying that because I‚Äôve cheated?
It‚Äôs okay. I know you know.
I wanted to be good enough for you.
You are, Tay. If anything, you‚Äôre TOO good.
Just because I cheated, doesn‚Äôt mean that I don‚Äôt love you.
I just haven‚Äôt loved you enough.
